        <h1>Gandhigiri</h1>
        <p>
            The Gandhigiri Event is a celebration of innovative minds and technological advancements. Organized by the CSE/IT department 
            of Axis Institute of Technology and Management, the event brings together talented students to showcase their 
            <b>software</b> and <b>hardware projects</b> that aim to solve real-world problems.
        </p>

        <h2>Software Projects</h2>
        <p>
            The <b>software projects</b> presented at Gandhigiri range from web applications to mobile apps and AI-based solutions.
            Students are encouraged to develop innovative software solutions that focus on automation, social good, and improving 
            everyday life. 
        </p>

        <h2>Hardware Projects</h2>
        <p>
            In the <b>hardware projects</b> category, students showcase their engineering skills by designing hardware solutions to everyday challenges.
            Projects in this category demonstrate creativity and technical expertise in building functional prototypes.
            
        </p>
        

        <h2>Bringing Innovation to Life</h2>
        <p>
            The <b>Gandhigiri Event</b> not only highlights technical skills but also promotes teamwork and collaboration. By tackling
            real-world challenges, these projects serve as stepping stones for students aspiring to make a mark in the tech industry.
            The event emphasizes the importance of using technology for social good, in line with the values of non-violence and community service
            advocated by Mahatma Gandhi.
        </p>
